- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not explicitly mention computer vision, the DIP framework has been widely used in image processing tasks, and the extension to one-dimensional signals can be seen as a generalization of the original idea. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper does not directly relate to social networks, but the proposed method can be applied to various types of temporal signals, including sensor measurements, which can be seen as a type of network data. 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper specifically mentions audio signals as one of the types of signals that can be processed using the proposed method. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the challenge of avoiding overfitting in the proposed method, which can be seen as a problem related to information theory.
